reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Problem Promptly Address
reviews.reviewText: I've been taking these vitamins for two years without any issues. The vitamins are a liquid filled capsule to improve absorption. My last order arrived with a sticky substance coating the capsules. I use a pill case and the sticky coating transferred to the inside of the case. The pill case became sticky enough to "glue" small medications to its walls. I didn't notice this at first and missed several medications as a result. I contacted Clinical Daily using eMail and informed them of the problem. They replied two days later and offered to send me a replacement, I accepted. Two days later the replacement arrived. They explained that if the vitamins are exposed to high heat the capsules can leak. I'm guessing that if vitamins are exposed to high heat they will degrade. As we enter the summer season delivery systems are going to, unavoidably, get hot. Exposed to this heat the vitamins may lose some of their potency and leak as a result. Amazon and Clinical Daily need to find a way to prevent this damage. I am very satisfied with the support I received and the resolution of my issue.
